[SN]TITLE[SN]
Hartlepool United 1-4 Luton Town

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Substitute striker Jack Marriott scored twice for Luton as they cruised to a win at Hartlepool.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Marriott replaced injured Craig Mackail-Smith in the first half as Jonathan Smith put Luton ahead after Luke Guttridge's effort was saved.
Rakish Bingham wasted two good chances for the hosts before Billy Paynter's diving header levelled it up.
Marriot scored twice in four minutes to extend the Hatters lead and Ollie Lee curled in from 25 yards in injury-time.
